Conditional statements:
-to make the set instruction(block of code)(conditional block) execute only when the given condition is True
Block of code: set of instructions
-it will execute only when the specific condition true
Condition: An expression that evaluate an result(True/False)
EX: console.log(5>6)
Methods:
If:
Syntax:
If(condition){
---block of code
}
EXAMPLE CODE:

	Ø let a=5
        let b=10
        if(a<b){
            document.write("hi hansi","<br>")
        }
        document.write("welcome to India")
Output:
Hi hansi
Welcome to India

If-else:
EXAMPLE CODE:

	Ø let a=5
        let b=10
        if(a>b){
            document.write("hi hansi","<br>")
        }else{
            document.write("Rishi","<br>")
        }
        document.write("welcome to India")

Output:
Rishi
welcome to India


Elseif
EXAMPLE CODE:
	Ø  age=prompt("enter your age?")
        name=prompt("enter your name?")
        if(age<18){
            alert(name + " you are too young to marry")
        }else if (age>35){
            alert(name + "you are too old to marry")
        }else{
            alert(name + " you are perfect to marry")
        }
Output:
if age is 18-35 you are perfect to marry

Switch:
EXAMPLE CODE:
	
	Ø  let a=prompt("Enter the score of 1st Player")
	        let b=prompt("Enter the score of 2nd Player")
	        if((a>300 || b>300) && a+b<500){
	            document.write("You are eligible to team up")
	        }else{
	            document.write("You are not eligible to team up")
	        }
